<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1164,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">
This is a small section comprising about 26 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[802,1056,1164,1190]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[919,981,1164,1189]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Species previously placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[151,326,1202,1228]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="109 - 131" refId="ref10037" refString="Pascher, A. (1904) Ubersicht uber die Arten der Gattung Gagea. Sitzungberichte des Deutschen naturwissenschaflichmedicischen Vereins fur Bohmen ' Lotos' 24: 109 - 131." type="journal article" year="1904">Pascher (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascher, A." box="[339,400,1202,1228]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="353 - 375" refId="ref10067" refString="Pascher, A. (1907) Conspectus Gagearum Asiae. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou 19: 353 - 375." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
) and subsequently by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stroh, G." box="[673,826,1202,1228]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="485 - 520" refId="ref10868" refString="Stroh, G. (1937) Die Gattung Gagea Salisb. Beihefte zum Botanischen Centralblatt 57: 485 - 520." type="journal article" year="1937">Stroh (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Uphof, J. C." box="[886,1039,1202,1228]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="163 - 176" refId="ref10976" refString="Uphof, J. C. (1958 - 1960) A review of the genus Gagea Salisb. I-III. Plantlife 14: 124 - 132, 151 - 161; 15: 163 - 176." type="journal article" year="1958">Uphof (1958</bibRefCitation>
–1960) in 
<emphasis box="[1166,1192,1203,1228]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
Platyspermum 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,220,1241,1266]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" sensu="lato">sensu</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
were placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Levichev, IG" box="[488,697,1241,1267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="917 - 951" refId="ref9667" refString="Levichev, IG. (2006) A review of the Gagea (Liliaceae) species in the flora of Caucasus. Botanicheskii Zhurnal 91: 917 - 951." type="journal article" year="2006">Levichev (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[760,1034,1241,1267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[877,941,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
in six sections: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Wolfe" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[1243,1325,1241,1266]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1243,1325,1241,1266]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Gagea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sections 
<taxonomicName authority="Boiss." authorityName="Boiss." authorityYear="1814" box="[151,419,1280,1306]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,330,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Platyspermum</emphasis>
Boiss.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[434,553,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Stipitatae</emphasis>
(Pascher) Davlianidze, 
<emphasis box="[857,988,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Bulbiferae</emphasis>
Levichev, 
<emphasis box="[1129,1305,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
Levichev, 
<emphasis box="[151,288,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Incrustatae</emphasis>
Levichev and 
<emphasis box="[470,654,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Dschungaricae</emphasis>
Levichev (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[791,1009,1318,1344]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[876,937,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." box="[1023,1270,1318,1344]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1135,1196,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). Analyses of nrITS and plastid sequences support neither Pascher’s nor Levichev's concept of 
<emphasis box="[1101,1127,1357,1382]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authority="G.F.Hoffmann, 1814" authorityName="G.F.Hoffmann" authorityYear="1814" box="[1194,1436,1357,1382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
Platyspermum 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1371,1436,1357,1382]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" sensu="lato">sensu</taxonomicNameLabel>
</taxonomicName>
lato
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[212,424,1396,1422]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[293,353,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). In the analyses of both combined datasets and separate nrITS and plastid sequences, 
<emphasis box="[151,179,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G.</emphasis>
sections 
<taxonomicName authority="Levichev" authorityName="Levichev" authorityYear="1814" box="[292,664,1434,1460]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Platyspermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis box="[292,542,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Platyspermum sensu</emphasis>
Levichev
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[677,848,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Graminifoliae</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[910,1048,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">Incrustatae</emphasis>
altogether comprise one highly supported clade (clade C; Figures 1–4 of 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[631,838,1473,1499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="125 - 142" refId="ref11349" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Fay, M. F., Ingrouille, M. J., Zarre, S. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2009) Molecular systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae; Liliales): implications of analyses of nuclear ribosomal and plastid sequences for infrageneric classification. Annals of Botany 104: 125 - 142." type="journal article" year="2009">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[710,768,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
). Clade C corresponds to clade A in the analyses of 
<emphasis box="[151,276,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">psbA-trnH</emphasis>
intergenic spacer, 
<emphasis box="[503,617,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">trnL-trnF</emphasis>
intergenic spacer and nrITS sequences conducted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peterson, A. &amp; Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J." pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="446 - 465" refId="ref10393" refString="Peterson, A., Levichev, I. G. &amp; Peterson, J. (2008) Systematics of Gagea and Lloydia (Liliaceae) and infrageneric classification of Gagea based on molecular and morphological data. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 46: 446 - 465." type="journal article" year="2008">
Peterson 
<emphasis box="[1375,1436,1512,1537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
. Clade C has 
<typeStatus box="[397,447,1550,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
I pedicel anatomy and 
<typeStatus box="[727,777,1550,1576]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
III basal leaf anatomy, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vvedensky" authorityYear="1946" box="[1319,1429,1551,1576]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Gagea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vegeta">
<emphasis box="[1319,1429,1551,1576]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">G. vegeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has 
<typeStatus box="[280,331,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
III pedicel anatomy and 
<typeStatus box="[636,687,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">type</typeStatus>
II leaf anatomy. All four pollen 
<typeStatus box="[1082,1145,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">types</typeStatus>
recognized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S." pageId="3" pageNumber="47" pagination="96 - 108" refId="ref11268" refString="Zarrei, M. &amp; Zarre, S. (2005) Pollen morphology of the genus Gagea (Liliaceae) in Iran. Flora 200: 96 - 108." type="journal article" year="2005">Zarrei &amp; Zarre (2005)</bibRefCitation>
occur in clade C. The constituent species of clade C were not resolved in the trees obtained from the analyses of malate synthase (
<bibRefCitation author="Zarrei, M. &amp; Wilkin, P. &amp; Ingrouille, M. J. &amp; Leitch, I. &amp; Buerki, S. &amp; Fay, M. F. &amp; Chase, M. W." box="[533,754,1666,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="47" refId="ref11421" refString="Zarrei, M., Wilkin, P., Ingrouille, M. J., Leitch, I., Buerki, S., Fay, M. F. &amp; Chase, M. W. (2010 a) Species relationships in the Gagea reticulata species complex utilizing nucleotide sequences of the low-copy nuclear gene malate synthase and flow cytometry data. Poster in SPNHC &amp; CBA - ABC Joint Conference, page 102, Ottawa, Canada." type="proceedings paper" year="2010">
Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[614,673,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2010a
</bibRefCitation>
) or ncpGS sequence data (Zarrei 
<emphasis box="[1148,1213,1667,1692]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="47">et al.,</emphasis>
unpubl. data).
</paragraph>
